General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 her authorized agent. A manufacturer who submits test results shall also submit a fee of ten
2 dollars ($10.00) for each test result to cover administrative costs."
3 SECTION 4. G.S. 18B-403.1(a) reads as rewritten:
4 "(a) Purchase-Transportation. – A person who is not a permittee may purchase and
5 transport for off-premises consumption a keg or kegs as defined in G.S. 18B-101(7c) after
6 obtaining a purchase-transportation permit. Failure to obtain a purchase-transportation permit
7 according to this section is a violation of G.S. 18B-303(b)."
8 SECTION 5. The ABC Commission shall adopt rules, or amend their rules,
9 consistent with the provisions of this act. The Commission may use the procedure set forth in
10 G.S. 150B-21.1 to adopt or amend any rules as required under this section.
11 SECTION 6. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to hemp-derived
12 beverages manufactured, sold, transported, imported, delivered, furnished, purchased, consumed,
13 or possessed on or after that date.
